class Solution {
public:
    string breakPalindrome(string palindrome) {
        int n = palindrome.size();
        if (n == 1) return "";

        for (int i = 0; i < n / 2; ++i) {
            if (palindrome[i] != 'a') {
                palindrome[i] = 'a';
                return palindrome;
            }
        }

        palindrome[n - 1] = 'b';
        return palindrome;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The approach iterates through the first half of the palindrome string. If a character is not 'a', it replaces it with 'a' to achieve the lexicographically smallest string. If all characters in the first half are 'a', it changes the last character to 'b' to ensure the string is not a palindrome.

